# Commerce Layer Agent TUI

Ink-based terminal UI (React rendered to terminal) for managing Commerce Layer API via natural language. Uses Vercel AI SDK (`ai` package) for streaming LLM responses and tool execution.

## Build & Run

```bash
npm run build   # tsc + chmod 755 build/index.js
npm run dev     # tsc --watch
npm start       # node build/index.js
```

No test runner or linter configured.

## Architecture

`index.tsx` → `<App>` (app.tsx) → config loading → view routing → `<ChatView>` with agent loop.

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Config | `src/config/` | Load/save `~/.config/cl-agent/config.json` (mode 0600), `ConfigProvider` context |
| AI | `src/ai/` | `Agent` class wrapping `streamText()`, message history, max 10 steps/request |
| Tools | `src/tools/` | Registry merging built-in CL tools + MCP tools, `clFetch()` with auto-retry |
| Views | `src/views/` | ChatView, SetupWizard, SettingsView, AccountManager |
| Components | `src/components/` | InputBar, ChatMessage, ConfirmDialog, HeaderBar, EnvBadge, RichText |
| Hooks | `src/hooks/` | useAgent, useConfig, useRouter, useKeybindings |

## Key Patterns

- Chat entries: discriminated union `user | assistant | tool_call | tool_result | info | error`, capped at 120
- Mutation flow: tool calls `requireConfirm()` → `ConfirmDialog` → user y/n → `UserDeclinedError` on decline
- MCP tools: stdio or SSE, destructive tools auto-wrapped with confirmation via regex detection
- Providers: Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, OpenRouter, Vercel AI Gateway
